Eldon Industries Inc expects a recordJuly 12 second quarter, Chairman Robert Silverstein told theNew York Society of Security Analysts.    The company's previous best second quarter was the periodended July 12, 1986 when Eldon had earnings of 1,353,000 dlrs,or 31 cts a share on sales of 20.7 mln dlrs.    Silverstein said, "If these positive trends continue, welook forward to favorable quarterly comparisons for the balanceof the year, resulting in another record year in sales andincome." Reuter&#3;